    "description": "Banaras Langda Mango is known for its unique taste, size, colour and fragrance. It has several uniqueness like highest pulp to stone ratio. The fruits are sweet and fleshy and maintain its green color after ripening. It is a good source of vitamin A, C , E and Iron and helps in maintenance of appropriate cholesterol level, skin cleansing, alkalizing body, increase virility in men, improve eye sight, aids good digestion, prevents heat stroke, strengthening immune system",
    "history": "The Langda mango is said to have originated in Varanasi in the 18th century, with the original tree reportedly grown by a lame (langda) fakir near the Ganga ghats. The variety spread through the region as its exceptional taste became famous, and Varanasi emerged as the primary centre of production for this distinctively green-skinned mango.",
