    "makingProcess": "Langda mango trees are propagated by grafting on rootstocks and cultivated on traditional orchards in the Varanasi region. Fruits are allowed to ripen on the tree, harvested by hand with care to avoid bruising, and consumed fresh or processed into aam panna, pickle, and other products. No post-harvest ripening treatment is applied — the green colour is natural.",
