    "history": "Pilkhuwa in Hapur district developed as a textile printing centre in the 19th and early 20th centuries, with artisans combining locally woven cotton with hand block-printing to produce distinctive home furnishing fabrics. The town's proximity to Delhi made it an early supplier of printed cotton bed covers and furnishings to urban markets.",
