    "history": "Bone craft in Sambhal district has been practiced for centuries, with the artisan community developing expertise in carving and inlaying the horns and bones of naturally deceased animals. The craft is closely related to the town's ivory-carving tradition (which predated restrictions on ivory), with craftsmen transitioning to bone when ivory became unavailable.",
