    "history": "Jaunpur Imarti has a history of approximately 200 years, with the sweet's origins traced to the British colonial era when confectioners in Jaunpur developed their distinctive version of the imarti (a urad dal-based fried sweet soaked in sugar syrup). Jaunpur's version became famous for its specific colour, texture, and flavour, distinguishing it from imarti made elsewhere.",
    "uniqueness": "Jaunpur Imarti is distinguished by its characteristic deep amber-orange colour, flower/spiral shape, and a specific ratio of urad dal batter that achieves a simultaneously crispy exterior and soft interior. The prolonged frying process in pure desi ghee and the specific sugar syrup concentration used in Jaunpur produce a texture and flavour that cannot be replicated by following standard imarti recipes.",
